"{\n  \"text\": \"It's cold and wet where I live. So I wanted to make a video about water and the importance of quality water when you're fermenting. Tap water contains chlorine and oftentimes chloramines, which is a bonding of chlorine and ammonia. Chlorine is relatively unstable, it evaporates off pretty quickly. Chloramines do not. Chloramines are much more stable and they kind of pose a problem for fermenting because fermenters cannot have antibacterial agents in their water while they're trying to ferment. This is one of the things that will really stop you in your tracks. Tap water is kind of a no-go when it comes to fermenting. You need to use distilled water or mineral water spring water, I'm sorry. Purified water tends to rely upon the filtration system, which oftentimes isn't as good as you may think. So I recommend not using purified water when fermenting, but definitely try to, you know, make sure your water is of high quality while fermenting because it is important. Thanks.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" It's cold and wet where I live.\",\n      \"start\": 0.64,\n      \"end\": 2.72,\n      \"duration\": 2.08,\n      \"confidence\": 0.992,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" It\",\n          \"start\": 0.64,\n          \"end\": 0.8,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.996\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"'\",\n          \"start\": 0.8,\n          \"end\": 0.96,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"s\",\n          \"start\": 0.96,\n          \"end\": 1.12,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" col\",\n          \"start\": 1.12,\n          \"end\": 1.28,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"d\",\n          \"start\": 1.28,\n          \"end\": 1.44,\n          \"duratio